        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 6:43PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 643 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northwest of Uptown Charlotte, or near Paw Creek, moving north
at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Huntersville, Northeast Charlotte, Northwest Charlotte, University
City, Paw Creek, Hidden Valley, East Charlotte, Central Charlotte,
and Croft.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
